jobDescription:
QBE Insurance Group Ltd is one of the world's top 20 general insurance and reinsurance companies, with operations in all the key insurance markets. QBE is listed on the Australian Securities Exchange and is headquartered in Sydney employing more than 17,000 people in 48 countries. 

This newly established global senior executive position will be responsible for:
•Working with the CEO and Global Diversity Council to develop and implement the diversity & inclusion strategy for QBE to achieve stated business goals and be recognised as an employer of choice globally;
•Ensure diversity and inclusion initiatives and policies are aligned globally across the business;
•Build and sustain strategic partnerships with diversity and inclusion organisations and networks in order to achieve QBE’s diversity and inclusion objectives; and
•Deliver appropriate collateral / material that communicates to internal and external audiences QBE’s commitment to diversity and inclusion and the tangible examples of how this is being bought to life.

description:
Pragmatic, creative and commercially focussed professional with over 19 years of HR work experience 11 in leadership and management roles.  My career history has solid grounding in extensive human resources generalist experience, enhanced by specialist Organisational Development and Inclusion & Diversity repertoires.  
I have a broad range of business exposure having worked across public and corporate sectors across many industries including, mining, transport and planning, Higher Education, telecommunications, media, legal, property and FCMG. I possess a complementary blend of project management, Organisational Development, HR strategic planning,marketing, diversity, sales, operations, communications, finance and governance skills.
Strengths:	
•	A skilled and adaptive change manager with proven ability to drive people management outcomes to improve business performance;
•	Capacity to build partnerships to empower managers and leaders to succeed in their challenges, 
•	Skills in transforming strategy into pragmatic, hands on outcomes, which are positive and measurable;
•	Capacity to mediate and negotiate through the myriad of HR legislations and expectations;
•	Proficiency around communications of goals, desires, designs and ambitions of the organisation at individual and team levels to all stakeholders irrespective of seniority or technicality; 
•	An understanding of what it takes to secure stakeholder engagement and buy in to achieve traction across large multifaceted organisations.

With a proven career experience combined with HR qualifications, I am a certified professional (CAHRI) member of the Australian Human Resources Institute and currently sit on it's national Inclusion and Diversity Reference Panel.

