QBE Insurance Group Limited is one of the top 20 insurers and reinsurers worldwide with operations in all key global insurance markets. QBE is an Australian listed company with  operations in 37 countries and more than 14,000 staff worldwide. 

Colin was a member of the QBE Global Group Executive from 2011 to 2017 holding a number of different roles including Group Chief Operating Officer and CEO of QBE Australia and New Zealand. As Group COO, he was directly responsible for facilitating profitable growth, including implementing operational excellence initiatives and strategies. 

His global areas of responsibility included: 

•	Global Information Technology alignment;
•	Global Shared Service Centre;
•	Data and Analytics;
•	Procurement;
•	Global Claims; and 
•	QBE’s Bermuda-based captive reinsurer, Equator Re.

Prior to being Group COO, Colin was the CEO of QBE’s Australian and New Zealand Operations.  With over 26 years’ experience in the general insurance industry, he has held a variety of executive level roles covering distribution, operations and marketing. During his 17 years with QBE he helped shape the vision and values of the organisation and successfully executed on multiple business objectives. 

Colin was Chairman of Equator Re, QBE's Bermuda-based captive reinsurer and Director of various QBE subsidiaries.
